23/05/2010
PODGORICA, Montenegro -- Montenegro marked the fourth anniversary of its independence on Friday (May 21st).
On this date in 2006, the republic held a referendum in which citizens opted for separation from the state union with Serbia.
In a speech marking the occasion, Prime Minister Milo Djukanovic said that Montenegro is recognised as "an oasis of multiethnic democracy in the Balkans".
(RTCG, RTS, Radio Free Europe, B92, Xihnua - 21/05/10)
